The Cs for NiSrS/GQD-5%//AC ASC device through CV was 249.2 C/g and through GCD was 267.3 C/g as indicated in Fig. 10
                     (a) and (b). Stability performance for NiSrS/GQD-5%//rGO ASC device was determined through performing GCD measurements at 5 A/g for 10,000 cycles, as shown in Fig. 10(c). After 10,000 cycles, the device retained an excellent capacitance of 98.3 % and an exceptional columbic efficiency of 100 %. This research showed increased columbic efficiency and capacity retention then previously reported literature (Table 2
                     ). This demonstrates the exceptional cycle stability and electrochemical performance of NiSrS/GQD-5%//AC. Two critical factors in evaluating supercapacitor performance for practical applications are energy density and power density. The energy density and power density of the NiSrS/GQD-5%//AC ASC device was Equations (3) and (4) are used to compute Ed and Pd. The related Ragone plot was shown in Fig. 10(d). At a power density of 1750 W/kg, the NiSrS/GQD-5%//AC had a greater energy density of 44 Wh/kg. A higher power density of 4800 W/kg was attained at an average energy density of 5 Wh kg−1. The results obtained exceed any published reports current research for NiS materials, illustrating a significant increase in supercapacitor performance (Table 3
                     ).
